				\begin{document}$$c_{j,k}^{i}$$\end{document} is the connection element. The knowledgebase of ESN is a group of connection matrices (presented by equation (1)) that links between knowledge layers. The knowledgebase of ESN can be easily modified by adding, deleting and/or updating knowledge layers, classes and associated parameters of each class applying flowchart shown in Fig. 4. The modification of developed ESN does not require a complete reconstruction of ESN. The ESN structure allow dynamic change of its knowledgebase whenever it is required. Energy expertise encode their knowledge in the connection matrices according to the building energy case of interest. The more new cases have been encoded in the knowledgebase, the more the knowledgebase expands. A well-developed ESN represents knowledge pool of energy expertise that can be used effectively by unexperienced persons. The following algorithm is used to form the ESN using the matrix presentation.
