The full presentation of the matrix elements indicates the connection of all the classes in predecessor layer with the sub-classes in the successor layer.
The elements replaced by 0 indicate no connection between classes.
The elements replaced by 1 indicate the class is related to the predecessor class however, it has no design parameters (descriptive only).
There is no direct connection between two non-adjacent classes.
If a connection between two non-adjacent classes is required, an additional replicate of the parent class is inserted within the intermediate classes with a connection arrow and element value of 1 indicating no design parameters.
