The objective of the case study is to demonstrate implementation of ESN and highlight the expected outcomes. As the proposed ESN is generic; the building structure and hence, associated profiles of heat demand, electricity demand, and energy sources can be easily adjusted according to the case under study without effecting the validity of the methodology. A simplified structure, rectangular Prism, residential house, located in Toronto area, is used as a case study for ESN development. The house is a three stories with dimensions 10×7×9m3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
